  <summary>Sets the volume of the sound played by the <command tag="beep">beep</command> <glossary tag="command">command</glossary>.</summary>
  <examples>
    <example>set the beepLoudness to 0</example>
    <example>set the beepLoudness to 50</example>
    <example>put the beepLoudness into storedBeepVolume</example>
  </examples>
  <description>
    <p>Use the <b>beepLoudness</b> <glossary tag="property">property</glossary> to vary the volumne of the beep, in order to increase or decrease its urgency.</p><p/><p><b>Value:</b></p><p>The <b>beepLoudness</b> is an <keyword tag="integer">integer</keyword> between zero and 100.</p><p/><p><b>Comments:</b></p><p>Set the <b>beepLoudness</b> to -1 to use the <keyword tag="default">default</keyword> system setting.</p><p/><p>The <b>beepLoudness</b> has no effect on <glossary tag="Mac OS">Mac OS</glossary> or <glossary tag="Windows">Windows systems</glossary>, and on some <glossary tag="Unix">Unix systems</glossary> which don't allow changing the beep loudness.</p>
